# Generative AI Project: GAN vs VAE on MNIST

This repository contains my Generative AI project focused on comparing Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and Variational Autoencoders (VAEs) for generating handwritten digit images from the MNIST dataset.

## Project Overview
The main goal of this project is to study and compare two important generative models:
- Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs)
- Variational Autoencoders (VAEs)

The project evaluates their ability to generate realistic digit images and highlights their differences in training behavior, output quality, and generative performance.

## Dataset
- MNIST handwritten digits dataset

## Repository Structure
- `notebooks/` → Jupyter notebook used for experiments and training
- `src/` → Python source code version of the project
- `presentation/` → project presentation slides
- `results/` → generated samples, plots, and result images
- `requirements.txt` → required Python libraries
- `README.md` → project documentation

## Methods Used
- Data preprocessing
- Model design and training
- Image generation
- Visual comparison of results
- GAN vs VAE performance discussion

## Files
- `notebooks/ParisaIzadiyar_GI_Prj.ipynb`
- `src/parisaizadiyar_gi_prj.py`
- `presentation/ParisaIzadiyar_GI_Prj_GAN_VAE.pptx`

